channel.title: Fender Stratocaster Guitar
channel.description:
1. I decided to make a model of a Fender Stratocaster guitar, which I own :)
2. I already know there are over a hundred guitar models on this forum
3. I traced over half of this model
4. I would like some comments and/or feedback

item.title: Fender Stratocaster Guitar
item.dc:creator: @reyx7 reyx7
item.description:
@reyx7 wrote:

[quote=“ravens, post:3, topic:423041”]i think the wireframe looks like that because it is triangulated for rsps client.
i would say it looks great 1 suggestion, change greenish blue color to something better, if you are going for realism. if you just want it to look cool then keep it.[/quote]

If you ever have zig zags like that going across the body, it’s been traced.

item.title: Fender Stratocaster Guitar
item.dc:creator: @Cole1497 Cole1497
item.description:
@Cole1497 wrote:

It’s not triangulated for rsps; look at the size.The wireframe proves that this was mostly traced.
Primitives give a better wireframe and overall a better model.

item.title: Fender Stratocaster Guitar
item.dc:creator: @ravens ravens
item.description:
@ravens wrote:

i think the wireframe looks like that because it is triangulated for rsps client.
i would say it looks great 1 suggestion, change greenish blue color to something better, if you are going for realism. if you just want it to look cool then keep it.

item.title: Fender Stratocaster Guitar
item.dc:creator: @reyx7 reyx7
item.description:
@reyx7 wrote:

Start over… the wireframe is rather horrendous. Try manipulating prims, you’ll find a better, more efficient structure and poly count. The overall model LOOKS nice, but on the inside it’s rather a mess.
